I understand your point of view, of not liking changes this late in the game. But I still hold the position that very little will change for the pierce shade. The targets that you have gone after with good results will still be weak against thrust damage. The classes that have been a big no-no are still going to be off limits. So how does this change anything to an appreciable degree? Like I posted in another thread there are 14 classes that the pierce shade can go after. Thats 14 out of 22 possible classes you can go after, what more do you want?<br>
<br>
So it boils down to if you are a nightshade it is very much in your favor to go pierce. You dont have to go pierce, and you can opt to go blades, but from a benifits standpoint pierce is where its at. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubrendelblackhammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brendel Blackhammer</A> at: 7/28/02 5:13:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaiyasamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maiya Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/28/02 7:00:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3824.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What are the options  for a Luri Shade now?</span><hr size=1> Actually, with the new changes to armor resistances, a pierce Nightshade's ability to kill archers has been hindered, while a slash Infiltrator or any Shadowblade has had their selection of targets increased because of the resistances on scale armor.<br>
